- `locallyConsistent (List.toFinset (PreState.forms a✝ bt π))`: This means that no formula `φ` and its negation `¬φ` are both in the set. This is a standard condition for consistency.
- `Sequent.basic (PreState.last a✝ bt π)`: This means that the last formula in the sequence `π.last` is a basic one (i.e., an axiom or a simple assumption). This is typically proven by induction or by using properties of the sequence construction.

